1/6/00
  Found a bug in the PCR detection:
    Clean cut uses detection of first slice start code to detect beginning
    of a picture.  If this takes more than 1 TP, then the PCR detected at the
    first TP will be counted for the previous picture, which is wrong.
    This problem only appears with the new clean cut module which detect
    both picture start and sequence end code.

  Solution: (Version dpi132.fls) 
    Move PCR detection code from bufferer to switcher
    No longer need the pcrFlag field in PicStat.
    No longer need to have the tbOffset field in PicStat.  The tbOffset in
    ChanInfo will be used.


1/7/00
  Found a bug in picture based splicing:
    If we start to search for exit picture when the designated number of frames
    have been seen in the foreground channel, we may have missed the last frame
    in the channel.  Instead we should be using the temporal reference to detect
    the last picture.  If the incoming picture's TR - reference picture's TR
    >= the designated number of frames, then we should start looking for
    exit frame.


