1/13/00
  Found a potential problem in output Task:  channel turnned off at last
  video frame without checking whether audio is ready.
  Solution: two flags, videoDone and audioDone are added to ChanInfo.
  Both video and audio will check whether both flags are set, and if so,
  call signalSpliceIndication() to turn off channel and send splice indication
  message.  For video case, the output task will do this after output the
  last video frame.  For audio, the audio switcher will do this after
  moving the last audio TP away from pidChansHandle. 

  BUG: forgot to send indication in some FORCE SWITCH cases.

  BUG: in FORCE SWITCH case, the indication is sent too early.  Should postpone
       until all video/audio is sent.


