1/24/00
  Try to make sure the DPI code can function as ratemux:
    - Mux (ver 107): turn off DPI flag, turn on drift correction,
           enable "No data warning message".
    - Demux (ver 142): turn off DPI flag.

  Problem: Lots of drift warning message.
    The drift is due to the fact that some picture may not come with a PCR.
    As a result, the old value in PicStat is used to calculate drift, which
    is wrong.  This problem happens on Harmonic Lightway but not DiviCom.
  Solution: use previous picture PCR and local TS if no PCR is sent
    for current picture

  Noticed a significant increase in free PidBuf when Mux delay is reduced
    from 3/4 sec to 1/2 sec.


1/25/00
  Noticed that the mux BL seems to be propotional to the channel bitrate!
  The reason is that the mux try to send to the decoder as much pictures
  as possible (max decoder buffer fullness).  In lower bandwidth channel,
  more pictures can be sent.  Therefore the lower bandwidth channel has
  less picture waiting in the demux buffer.
  Notice also that the scheduler runs in quarter second interval.  If the
  channel miss a chance, it needs to wait 1/4 sec, which means about 7 frames
  will be added to its queue.
  One ultimate way to solve this is to realign the channel delay by dropping
  pictures once the channel starts in the mux.  May cause initial interruption
  but maximize throughput.

  Trying to harmonize rc.h and rc5.h so I can switch rate control algorithm
  by just selecting a number for RATECNTL in the Makefile.


1/26/00
  Try to temporarily stop the bufferer task from draining the PidBuf
  when the free pidbuf level is too low.  This way other task can still
  allocate message buffer.  Otherwise other task will be halt.
  At 30 Mbps, about 20,000 packets arrive per second.

  This trick increases the max bypass input rate from 20 to about 30 Mbps.


